{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, we can use the following theorem to obtain strong Lipschitz non-regularity from strong non-surjectivity of Em (see Corollary 4.6 for the explicit statement).",
    "Theorem 4.4 (Predual separation theorem).Let X and Y be Banach spaces and T: X → Y * a bounded linear operator, which is additionally strongly non-surjective.",
    "Then there exists a sequence v n ∈ Y such that(i) ∥v n ∥ Y ≥ 1, (ii) sup x∈B X |⟨T (x), v n ⟩| ≤ 1 n. Proof.",
    "Let K = T (B X).",
    "Since B X is absolutely convex and T is linear, K is also absolutely convex."
  ]
}